meanings.definition: Defeated in a competition or contest by being more skillful or clever.
meanings.sent1: The outduelled team graciously accepted their loss.
meanings.sent2: The outduelled chess player congratulated the winner.
meanings.sent3: The outduelled squirrel tried a new strategy next time.
meanings.sent4: Her outduelled performance in the race left her determined to train harder.
meanings.sent5: The outduelled magician learned new tricks to improve.

meanings.definition: To surpass in a competition or contest by being more skillful or clever.
meanings.sent1: She outduelled her opponent with a brilliant move.
meanings.sent2: The skilled archer outduelled all others in the competition.
meanings.sent3: The cat outduelled the mouse in a playful game of chase.
meanings.sent4: His determination to outduel his rival led to hours of practice.
meanings.sent5: The detective outduelled the criminal in a battle of wits.
